main event: Sighting of unidentified lights over Killeen, Texas on July 7, 1964
interesting points: The sighting involved multiple military personnel from the Killeen Base area
The objects were described as a formation of lights, with three in front and two others in formation
A second sighting involved a single light and an orange blob, with the object estimated to be around 2,000 feet in altitude
The objects were reported to move from south to north and would disappear in the distance or behind trees
The lights were described as white and estimated to be around 500-1,000 feet in altitude
sighted object: formation of lights, single light and orange blob
